<TITLE> Local trader killed by robbers in Kishoreganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoreganj, Aug 18 (bdnews24.com)  A local trader was killed in his home and four people injured after a gang of armed robbers attacked three houses in a Kishoreganj village on Tuesday, police said. The deceased was 47-year old Nani Gopal Chandra Saha of Halimpur village in Bajitpur upazila, said police sub-inspector Abu Sayeed Locals said the robbers entered Saha's house, stabbed him to death and stole 10 bhoris of gold and Tk 20,000. Saha's mother Nirmala Saha, 75, and son Sumon Chandra Saha, 20, were also injured by the robbers. The gang went to other houses in the neighbourhood and looted another 32 bharis of gold and Tk 42,000, locals said. Two people, named by villagers as Masud and Rukon, were injured as they tried to obstruct the robbers. Bajitpur police sub-inspector Sayeed said they were trying to arrest the robbers. bdnews
